      "body" : "@laanwj It depends on your TCP/IP stack settings. In FreeBSD, for example, sometimes it's recommended to set net.inet.tcp.recvspace parameter to 8k. With such receive buffer size you can get a significant improvement even for a local instance of bitcoind, speed up looks like a linear function of compression ratio.",
